
[1]malevolent

   MALEV'OLENT, a. Having an evil disposition towards another or others;
   wishing evil to others; ill disposed, or disposed to injure others. A
   malevolent heart rejoices in the misfortunes of others.

   1. Unfavorable; unpropitious; bringing calamity.
